\begin{aligned}
&(x - 1) + (x - 2) + (x - 3) + (x - 4)\\
&=(x + x + x + x) + (-1 - 2 - 3 - 4)\\
&=4x-10\\
&=x\\
\end{aligned}

So we are left with 4x - 10 = x. Now, let's solve for x by moving all the x terms on the left-hand side:
\begin{aligned}
&4x - x = 10\\
&3x = 10\\
&x = \frac{10}{3}
\end{aligned}

Therefore, the value of x is $\frac{10}{3}$.</th>
